in other words, for n > 2 players, the number of monotone and non-degenerate mechanisms becomes exponential in n. proposition 3. the number of monotone non-  degenerate k-action mechanisms in an n-player game is exponential in n, even if |a| = 2. 
the hardness stems from the fact that the necessary conditions we specified before for the optimality of the mechanisms (i.e., non-degenrate and monotone  allocations) are not restrictive enough for the general model.
