the reason why mutually-maximizer strategies maximize the expected social value in monotone mechanisms is intuitive: consider some action i (row in the matrix representation) for player 1. in a monotone mechanism, the allocation in such a row will be of the form [a, a, ..., b, b] (assuming that b 2 a).
we define the notion of  mutuallymaximizer thresholds, and show that threshold strategies based on such thresholds are optimal.
